x4freetext: The Be-14 and B-14 secondary beams were produced via
fragmentation of a 63 MeV/A O-18 primary beam on a
achieved via time-of-flight through the LISE
The beam was tracked onto a 275 mg/cm2 carbon target
SISD- The Si elements were placed 16 cm from the
target and consisted of two 500 mum thick 2.5*2.5 cm**2
Neutrons were detected using the Demon array
The main systematic error in the determination of the
cross section comes from the uncertainty in the angular
distribution fall-off factor used in the Monte Carlo
